==Swedish==

===Adverb===
'''jo'''
#[[yes]]; in disagreement with the last speaker.
#:''Du har inte borstat tänderna, eller hur? - Jo, (det har jag)''
#:''You haven't brushed your teeth, have you? - Yes, I have''

====Usage notes====
''jo'' is used instead of ''[[ja]]'' if the answer ''ja'' to a question could be ambigious - for example in the example above a answer ''ja'' could either be interpreted as a agreement with the person asking, or it could be considered as a confirmation that one really did brush the teeth. The word ''jo'' removes the possibility to agree with the speaker. In northern Sweden it is not uncommon for the word ''jo'' to be used in place of ''ja'' in all cases, in spoken language.

